Source: makehuman-dev
Section: graphics
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Joel Palmius <joepal1976@hotmail.com>
Build-Depends: devscripts, debhelper (>=9)
Standards-Version: 3.9.5
Homepage: http://www.makehuman.org

Package: makehuman-targets-dev
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, makehuman-targets
Conflicts: makehuman-data
Description: Raw targets for MakeHuman.
 These are the unprocessed targets for MakeHuman. It is unlikely
 you want to install these unless you plan to develop new targets
 using MakeTarget.

Package: makehuman-clothes-dev
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, makehuman-clothes
Conflicts: makehuman-data
Description: Raw obj and mhclo files for MakeHuman clothes.
 These are the unprocessed obj files for MakeHuman clothes. It is
 unlikely you want to install these unless you plan to modify
 existing clothes. Specifically you do not need this for making
 completely new clothes.

Package: makehuman-hair-dev
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, makehuman-hair
Conflicts: makehuman-data
Description: Raw obj files for MakeHuman hair.
 These are the unprocessed obj files for MakeHuman hair. It is
 unlikely you want to install these unless you plan to modify
 existing hair. Specifically you do not need this for making
 completely new hair.

Package: makehuman-bodyparts-dev
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, makehuman-bodyparts
Conflicts: makehuman-data
Description: Raw obj files for MakeHuman bodyparts.
 These are the unprocessed obj files for MakeHuman bodyparts. It is
 unlikely you want to install these unless you plan to modify
 existing bodyparts. Specifically you do not need this for making
 completely new bodyparts.

Package: makehuman-proxymeshes-dev
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, makehuman
Conflicts: makehuman-data
Description: Raw obj and proxy files for MakeHuman proxies.
 These are the unprocessed files for MakeHuman proxies. It is
 unlikely you want to install these unless you plan to modify
 existing proxies. Specifically you do not need this for making
 completely new proxies.

Package: makehuman-3dobjs-dev
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, makehuman
Conflicts: makehuman-data
Description: Raw files for the base mesh.
 These are the unprocessed files for MakeHuman base mesh. It is
 unlikely you want to install these unless you plan to modify
 the base mesh (which is probably a bad idea).

